Additional Functions for Formulas

The case function handles if/then logic for formulas. The syntax is: case primary_expr(optional) when condition then result_expr ... else default_expr end.

The coalesce function returns the first non-null value in an expression. Otherwise, returns null. The syntax is: coalesce(expr1,expr2).
